=== National Championships ===
Over the course of its existence, ACC schools have captured 12 NCAA men's basketball championships. [[North Carolina Tar Heels men's basketball|North Carolina]] has won five, [[Duke Blue Devils basketball|Duke]] has won four, [[NC State Wolfpack|North Carolina State]] has won two, and [[University of Maryland athletics|Maryland]] has won one. In addition, 8 of the 12 members have advanced to the [[NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Championship#Final Four|Final Four]] at least once.

In women's basketball, the ACC has won two national championships, with [[North Carolina Tar Heels women's basketball|North Carolina]] and [[Maryland Terrapins women's basketball|Maryland]]. In 2006, Duke, Maryland, and North Carolina all advanced to the [[NCAA Women's Division I Basketball Championship|Final Four]], the first time a conference placed three teams in the women's Final Four. Both 2006 NCAA women's finalists were from the ACC, with Maryland defeating Duke for the title.

