=== Bowl Games ===
Within the [[Bowl Championship Series]], the [[Orange Bowl (game)|Orange Bowl]] serves as the home of the ACC champion against another BCS at-large selection unless the conference's champion is selected for the national championship game.

The other bowls pick ACC teams in the order listed. The [[ACC Championship Game]] runner-up is guaranteed to fall no lower than the [[Sun Bowl]], the 4th pick, in the conference bowl hierarchy.<ref>http://espn.go.com/blog/acc/post/_/id/7643/new-acc-bowl-selection-process-in-effect-for-2010</ref> Previously the ACC Championship Game runner-up had been guaranteed the [[Music City Bowl]] with usually then the 5th pick.<ref>http://www.theacc.com/sports/m-footbl/spec-rel/112508aaa.html</ref>  The other rule change that will be in effect for the next four years is that the ACC has eliminated the clause in the contract that states if a bowl team has already selected the runner-up, it doesn't have to choose it again. <ref>http://espn.go.com/blog/acc/post/_/id/7643/new-acc-bowl-selection-process-in-effect-for-2010</ref>

Moreover, a bowl game can bypass a team in the selection process only if the two teams in question are within one game of each other in the overall ACC standings. This rule was instituted in response to concerns over the 2005 bowl season, in which Atlantic Division co-champion Boston College fell to the then last-pick [[MPC Computers Bowl]] (the MPC Computers Bowl is now the [[Humanitarian Bowl]]).

The following is the bowl selection order starting in 2010 and through 2013 and the teams involved in each bowl.
