== Lacrosse ==
=== National Championships ===
Since [[1971 NCAA Division I Men's Lacrosse Championship|1971]], when the first men's national champion was determined by the NCAA, the ACC has won 11 [[NCAA Men's Lacrosse Championship|national championships]], more than any other conference in [[college lacrosse]], including at least one by every team currently playing in the ACC. [[Virginia Cavaliers men's lacrosse|Virginia]] and [[North Carolina Tar Heels men's lacrosse|North Carolina]] have each won four national championships, [[Maryland Terrapins men's lacrosse|Maryland]] has won two, and [[Duke Blue Devils men's lacrosse|Duke]] has won one. In addition, prior to the establishment of the NCAA tournament, Maryland had won nine national championships while Virginia won two.

[[Women's lacrosse]] has only awarded a [[NCAA Women's Lacrosse Championship|national championship since 1982]], and the ACC has won more titles than any other conference. In all, the ACC has won 13 women's national championships: Maryland has won ten and Virginia has won three.

